.TH GAT-WATCH 1 "2026-06-04" "gat 0.3.0" "gat Manual"
.SH NAME
gat-watch \- continuously render the worktree list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gat watch
.RB [ \-\-interval
.IR ms ]
.RB [ \-\-once ]
.RB [ \-\-full ]
.RB [ \-\-fast ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Clears the screen and redraws the
.BR gat\-list (1)
table on an interval. Defaults to fast mode (skipping expensive checks) so it
stays responsive with many worktrees. Ctrl+C restores the cursor and exits
cleanly.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-interval " ms"
Refresh interval in milliseconds (default 1000, minimum 100).
.TP
.B \-\-once
Render once and exit (useful for tests and scripts).
.TP
.B \-\-full
Include dirty/merged/change-stat checks.
.TP
.B \-\-fast
Skip expensive checks (default).
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.EX
gat watch
gat watch \-\-interval 2000 \-\-full
gat watch \-\-once
.EE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR gat (1),
.BR gat\-list (1),
.BR gat\-ui (1)
